{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-9a5732877f1f0891","input":{"filename":"kb_maintainer_action_report.md","title":"Knowledge Base Maintainer – Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Knowledge Base Maintainer – Prioritized Action Report (≤ 500 words)\n\n**Prepared:** 2026‑06‑18\n\n---\n\n## 1. Evidence & Context\n\nThe **dossier** confirms the Knowledge Base Maintainer role: *\"Finds KB gaps from recurring tickets and drafts article updates.\"*  \n\nAn **analyze_records** run (limit = 10) returned three high‑relevance items (total = 3, risk = 16, opportunity = 10.8):\n\n| ID | Title | Status | Impact | Risk | Summary |\n|----|-------|--------|--------|------|---------|\n| **32‑A** | Knowledge base maintainer priority case | **urgent** | 52 144 | 4 | Highest‑impact open item; gap‑analysis needed. |\n| **32‑C** | Knowledge base maintainer blocked follow‑up | **blocked** | 24 752 | 3 | Requires cross‑functional coordination before safe recommendation. |\n| **32‑B** | Knowledge base maintainer routine queue item | **in_review** | 12 616 | 3 | Lower‑risk operational item; useful for comparison. |\n\nRisk/Opportunity scores (higher = more critical) further prioritize **32‑A** (risk 8, opp 7) over **32‑C** (risk 5, opp 2.5) and **32‑B** (risk 3, opp 1.3).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Prioritized Actions (under 500 words total)\n\n### 🔥 **Action 1 – Immediate KB Gap Analysis (Item 32‑A)**\n- **Goal:** Close the highest‑impact KB gap, preventing recurrence of related tickets.\n- **Steps:**\n  1. Pull the last 30 days of tickets tagged *kb*/*support* (use ticketing API).\n  2. Identify recurring themes (≥ 3 occurrences) that lack documentation.\n  3. Draft a concise article outline per theme (title, problem, solution, FAQ).\n  4. Peer‑review with the senior support engineer (30 min sync).\n  5. Publish to the internal KB; tag the originating ticket for traceability.\n- **Owner:** Knowledge Base Maintainer (you).\n- **Timeline:** **48 h** from report receipt.\n- **Success Metric:** Reduction of related tickets by ≥ 20 % within 2 weeks.\n\n### ⏸️ **Action 2 – Unblock Follow‑up (Item 32‑C)**\n- **Goal:** Resolve dependency on the *Product Documentation* team.\n- **Steps:**\n  1. Schedule a 15‑min cross‑team meeting (support & product docs) to clarify required artifact format.\n  2. Document the agreed‑upon hand‑off checklist.\n  3. Assign a point‑person from each team to maintain the checklist.\n  4. Once cleared, treat the resulting KB update as **Action 3**.\n- **Owner:** Support Ops coordinator (or designate).\n- **Timeline:** **5 business days** (meeting + checklist).\n- **Success Metric:** Checklist approved; status changes from *blocked* to *in_progress*.\n\n### 📅 **Action 3 – Routine KB Refresh (Item 32‑B)**\n- **Goal:** Address lower‑risk, ongoing KB maintenance.\n- **Steps:**\n  1. Review tickets marked *kb* in the past quarter for minor gaps.\n  2. Batch‑update existing articles (spell‑check, link verification).\n  3. Log each edit in the KB change log.\n- **Owner:** Knowledge Base Maintainer (after Action 1 completes).\n- **Timeline:** **2 weeks** after Action 1.\n- **Success Metric:** Zero open *kb* tickets older than 30 days.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Assumptions & Risks\n- **Assumption:** Ticketing system provides tag filters and export capability.\n- **Assumption:** Peer‑review capacity is available within the 48‑hour window.\n- **Risk:** If the cross‑team meeting stalls, Action 2 may slip; mitigation is to set a firm deadline and involve a manager if needed.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Next Steps\n1. **Create a tracking board** (e.g., Jira Epic) with the three actions.\n2. **Notify** the Support Ops manager of the 48‑hour deadline for Action 1.\n3. **Monitor** ticket volume daily; update the board with impact metrics.\n\n---\n\n*Prepared by the Knowledge Base Maintainer agent (ID 32‑knowledge‑base‑maintainer).*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:20:28.661Z"}}
